My main criticism is that there's very little that isn't explained. The whole point of the SCPs is that we are terrified of the effect and know next to nothing of the cause. For example, the Sculpture, the very first SCP. I would suggest that as a template for any and all SCPs. While I may be remiss in a few of my own works, I think I did a very fine job with SCP-139 if I say so myself. If you notice in that one, the artifact is never actually even observably the cause of any incident. It's SCPs like this that are truly effective.

I would try to make this far more obtuse and oblique, therefore inciting more emotion and less intellectual stimulation.







