That assumes that 230 was weighed once and only once, and/or that the (in-universe) report has not been updated with new info since it was originally written. Neither scenario makes sense to me. More realistically, 230 (and most other living SCPs) would regularly have their vitals taken (daily or weekly), including height and weight, with the article updated as more data is collected and analyzed. In this case, a mass of "68.04lb).







